2C%20nightlife%20spending%20reached%2011%25%20above%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20a%20report%20from%20Mastercard%20found.%20It's%20not%20hard%20to%20understand%20why.%20Few%20people%20in%20the%20country%20lived%20as%20cramped%20an%20existence%20through%20the%20pandemic%20as%20New%20Yorkers%20did.%20Once%20it%20was%20over%2C%20they%20bet%20everything%20on%20the%20return%20of%20the%20institutions%20that%20form%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20city's%20culture.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20could%20keep%20their%20weak%20vibes.%20For%20New%20York%20City%2C%20a%20brush%20with%20death%20called%20for%20a%20time%20of%20decadence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20we%20are%20back%20to%20where%20we%20were%20pre-pandemic.%20Now%20more%20than%20ever%2C%20people%20are%20spending%2C%20and%20even%20more%20so%2C%20restaurants%20are%20opening%20back%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Sasue%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20new%2C%20hot%20restaurants%20opening%20every%20freaking%20week.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20that's%20what%20the%20city's%20doing%20now.%20Get%20into%20it.%20Clubsteraunts%20are%20back%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcook-chef-manager-amusement-parks-gen-z-attendant-experience-economy2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-worried-gen-z-doesnt-have-fun-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egeneration%20that%20claims%20to%20dislike%20fun%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-loneliness-spends-money-to-make-friends-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseen%20there%20in%20full%20force%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grubstreet.com%2Farticle%2Fbest-nyc-restaurants-2023-wild-creative-ambition-is-back.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecity's%20bistros%20have%20met%20this%20enthusiasm%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20upping%20their%20game.%20Chefs%20in%20New%20York%20have%20somehow%20yassified%20hard-boiled%20eggs%2C%20and%20LCD%20Soundsystem's%20frontman%20James%20Murphy%20has%20a%20restaurant%20that's%20selling%20them%20for%20%2425.%20Naturally%2C%20those%20eggs%20have%20caviar%20on%20them.%20There's%20caviar%20everywhere.%20At%20Coqodaq%2C%20a%20just-opened%20Korean%20fried%20chicken%20restaurant%20that%20looks%20like%20a%20Las%20Vegas%20church%2C%20you%20can%20order%20a%20perfectly%20crisped%20nugget%20with%20caviar%20on%20it.%20It%20will%20cost%20you%20%2428%20and%20whatever%20it%20takes%20you%20to%20get%20through%20a%20meal%20while%20watching%20packs%20of%20TikTok%20food%20influencers%20completely%20lose%20their%20minds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20kids%20might%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BNature%20is%20healing.%26quot%3B%20The%20city's%20affluent%20consists%20of%20the%20same%20Wall%20Street%20workhorses%2C%20fashion%20and%20public-relations%20power%20brokers%2C%20trust-fund%20babies%20(American%20and%20foreign)%2C%20chic%20people%2C%20quasi-creatives%20of%20advertising%2C%20total%20nerds%20of%20tech%2C%20and%20straight-up%2C%20never-sleeping%20hustlers%20%E2%80%94%20but%20their%20tastes%20have%20changed.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-members-only-nyc-social-club-zero-bond-9000-waitlist-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMembers-only%20social%20clubs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20restaurants%20abound.%20The%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faman-club-private-members-club-nyc-photo-tour-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAman%20New%20York%20has%20a%20private%20club%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20%24200%2C000%20initiation%20fee%2C%20and%20the%20boys%20who%20brought%20us%20Carbone%20have%20a%20private%20restaurant%20called%20ZZ's%20with%20a%20%2420%2C000%20initiation%20fee%20and%20%2410%2C000%20annual%20membership.%20There%20are%20the%20Casas%20%E2%80%94%20Cruz%20and%20Cipriani%20(both%20private%20clubs%2C%20no%20re