eady%20clip.%20Most%20recently%2C%20the%20famed%20chef%20Jean-Georges%20Vongerichten%20opened%20Four%20Twenty-Five%20on%20Park%20Avenue%2C%20where%20it%20feels%20like%20you%20are%20dining%20on%20a%20crystal%20cloud.%20It's%20a%20place%20to%20watch%20a%20very%20classic%20uptown%20New%20York%20City%20crowd%20%E2%80%94%20an%20older%20set%20of%20ultraprofessionals%2C%20mom%20and%20dad%20on%20date%20night%2C%20women%20who%20have%20enough%20money%20but%20too%20much%20self-awareness%20to%20be%20on%20%26quot%3BReal%20Housewives%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-lincoln-center-fundraiser-steve-cohen-new-york-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoney%20managers%20drinking%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20gorgeous%20bar%20after%20a%20late%20night%20at%20the%20office%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-hamptons-party-return-office-recession-stock-market-worries-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyes%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E).%20For%20these%20people%2C%20there%20must%20be%20elegance%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20of%20NYC%20nightlife%20is%20focused%20on%20making%20things%20fancy%3B%20some%20of%20it%20is%20just%20theatrical%20and%20fun.%20In%20the%20East%20Village%2C%20Paradise%20Lost%20transports%20patrons%20to%20a%20tiki%20bar%20located%20on%20a%20choppy%20beach%20near%20the%20capitol%20of%20Hell.%20It%20works%20because%20the%20drinks%20are%20a%20full-on%20show.%20The%20Saturn%2C%20a%20vintage%20gin%20cocktail%20that%20won%20the%201967%20IBA%20championship%2C%20comes%20smoking%20with%20dry%20ice.%20And%20if%20you%20order%20the%20Lady%20of%20the%20Beasts%2C%20you'll%20experience%20what%20the%20bar%20calls%20%26quot%3Bfire%20and%20show.%26quot%3B%20Bongo%20drums%20will%20ring%20out%20through%20the%20bar%2C%20and%20your%20server%20will%20present%20the%20cocktail%20to%20you%20in%20a%20dazzle%20of%20flames.%20The%20Lady%20is%20just%20one%20of%20a%20few%20cocktails%20on%20the%20menu%20that%20come%20with%20all%20of%20that%20drama.%20If%20there%20is%20a%20hard%20landing%20for%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20NYC%20will%20have%20to%20meet%20it%20with%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20hangover.%20After%20what%20the%20city%20went%20through%2C%20it%20will%20have%20been%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20full%20vibespace%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20survey%20of%20New%20York%20City's%20most%20glimmering%20restaurants%20and%20competitive%20cocktailers%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20an%20incomplete%20picture%20of%20how%20the%20city%20is%20recovering.%20The%20pandemic%20was%20a%20violent%20lesson%20in%20how%20an%20inflationary%20shock%20impacts%20the%20affluent%20much%20less%20than%20everyone%20else.%20And%20that%20makes%20for%20complex%20vibes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20from%20TouchBistro%2C%20a%20company%20that%20provides%20point-of-sales%20services%20to%20restaurants%2C%20NYC%20restaurant%20margins%20averaged%20around%209.2%25%20in%202023%2C%20down%20from%2010.1%25%20a%20year%20in%202022%20and%20just%20below%20the%20national%20average%20of%209.3%25.%20Food%20operators%20said%20they%20spent%2043%25%20more%20on%20food%20costs%20in%202023%20than%20they%20did%20in%202022%2C%20the%20highest%20jump%20in%20the%20country.%20And%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjanuary-jobs-report-labor-market-good-economy-inflation-wages-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployers%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%20%3C%2Fa%3Eare%20regaining%20the%20upper%20hand%2C%20staff%20turnover%20at%20NYC%20restaurants%20was%20around%2031%25%20in%202023.%20The%20national%20average%20turnover%20rate%20sat%20at%2028%25.%20Every%20restaurant%20is%20facing%20these%20issues%2C%20but%20businesses'%20ability%20to%20deal%20with%20increasing%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20while%20holding%20onto%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20varies%20greatly.%20A%20December%20survey%20from%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Hospitality%20Alliance%20found%20that%20while%2037%25%20of%20respondents%20felt%20positive%20about%20future%20business%20revenue%2C%2030%25%20percent%20of%20respondents%20were%20feeling%20pessimistic%20about%20the%20future%2C%20and%20another%2020%25%20felt%20uncertain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNew%20York%20City's%20restaurants%20and%20bars%20are%20experiencing%20an%20uneven%20pandemic%20recovery%20nearly%20four%20years%20after%20COVID-19%20struck%20our%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrew%20Rigie%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Hospitality%20Alliance%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20some%20have%20recovered%2C%20others%20still%20struggle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20industry%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-losing-rental-housing-crisis-combine-apartments-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emirror%20of%20the%20city%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20haves%20are%20being%20delighted%20in%20new%20dining%20rooms%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-expensive-home-250-million-nyc-penthouse-central-park-tower-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglittering%20new%20high-rises%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedian-wage-people-leaving-nyc-financial-pipe-dream-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave-nots%20are%20experiencing%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20trauma%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgothamist.com%2Fnews%2Fnyc-evictions-surged-in-2023-with-legal-lockouts-nearing-pre-covid-levels%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%20number%20of%20evictions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20in%20Brooklyn%20and%20The%20Bronx%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-rent-keeps-hitting-record-highs-despite-migration-from-city-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esqueeze%20of%20record-high%20rents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20No%20one%20seems%20to%20have%20an%20answer%20for%20New%20York's%20