Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fop-ed-manmohan-singh-a-tragic-figure-of-our-times-writes-yashwant-sinha-552302%5C%22%3EManmohan%20Singh%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20good%20man%20leading%20a%20bad%20government%20%E2%80%93%20personally%20admirable%20but%20politically%20inept%20and%20paralysed%20by%20the%20competing%20forces%20within%20his%20own%20party.%20Narendra%20Modi%20was%20the%20coming%20man%2C%20offering%20an%20energy%20and%20vision%20that%20the%20governing%20party%20simply%20couldn't%20match.%20The%20result%3A%20Congress%20was%20swept%20from%20power%20and%20lost%20more%20than%20three-quarters%20of%20its%20seats%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoing%20Down%20The%20Congress%20Way%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomething%20similar%20is%20now%20happening%20in%20British%20politics.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fcrushing-loss-in-uk-polls-predicted-for-rishi-sunak-led-conservative-party-5372671%5C%22%3ERishi%20Sunak%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20catastrophic%20election%20defeat.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frishi-sunaks-conservative-party-set-for-worst-election-defeat-in-uk-shows-new-survey-5368491%5C%22%3EThe%20Conservatives%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20in%20power%20for%20fourteen%20years%2C%20but%20fresh%20opinion%20polls%20suggest%20they%20will%20be%20humbled%20in%20the%20coming%20election%2C%20losing%20up%20to%20two-thirds%20of%20their%20seats%20in%20the%20UK%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERishi%20Sunak%20continues%20to%20put%20a%20brave%20face%20on%20his%20appalling%20polling%2C%20but%20his%20party%20has%20just%20about%20given%20up.%20Conservatives%20know%20they%20are%20about%20to%20be%20evicted%20from%20power%2C%20and%20many%20of%20their%20MPs%20are%20either%20scouting%20for%20new%20jobs%20or%20feuding%20viciously%20about%20who%20should%20lead%20the%20party%20after%20Sunak's%20almost%20inevitable%20departure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Britain's%20peculiar%2C%20and%20distinctly%20dilapidated%2C%20political%20system%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20discretion%20about%20when%20a%20general%20election%20is%20held.%20The%20last%20possible%20date%20is%20in%20January%20next%20year%3B%20the%20expectation%20is%20that%20the%20election%20will%20be%20in%20October%20or%20November%20this%20year.%20So%2C%20a%20note%20of%20caution%20%E2%80%93%20a%20lot%20can%20happen%20in%20that%20time%3A%20wars%2C%20scandals%2C%20crises%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20unexpected%20events.%20Nothing%20is%20certain%20in%20politics.%20But%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20odds%20that%20betting%20companies%20are%20offering%20on%20the%20election%20outcome%20%E2%80%93%20often%20a%20very%20reliable%20indicator%2C%20as%20they%20lose%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20if%20they%20get%20it%20wrong%20%E2%80%93%20they%20are%20putting%20the%20odds%20on%20the%20Labour%20opposition%20becoming%20the%20largest%20party%20in%20Parliament%20at%20more%20than%2090%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Really%20Went%20Wrong%20For%20Sunak%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20has%20gone%20wrong%20for%20Rishi%20Sunak%20in%20the%20eighteen%20months%20since%20he%20became%20prime%20minister%3F%20He%20had%20a%20lot%20going%20for%20him.%20He's%20seen%20as%20young%2C%20earnest%20and%20honest%3B%20in%20his%20time%20in%20office%2C%20inflation%20has%20fallen%20sharply%20and%20real%20wages%20have%20begun%20to%20grow%3B%20after%20the%20chaos%20of%20Boris%20Johnson's%20years%20in%20power%2C%20he%20has%20restored%20a%20measure%20of%20stability%20and%20competence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Sunak%20does%20not%20offer%20a%20political%20vision%3B%20he%20is%20indecisive%2C%20he%20presides%20over%20a%20deeply%20divided%20party%2C%20he%20has%20made%20a%20few%20appallingly%20bad%20decisions%2C%20and%2C%20above%20all%2C%20his%20political%20instincts%20are%20poor.%20When%20a%20prime%20minister%20makes%20public%20pledges%20and%20fails%20to%20deliver%20them%2C%20that%20really%20damages%20his%20standing.%20Rishi%20Sunak%20promised%20to%20cut%20the%20huge%20waiting%20lists%20for%20treatment%20in%20the%20publicly-funded%20health%20service%3B%20those%20waiting%20lists%20have%20continued%20to%20lengthen.%20He%20pledged%20to%20%E2%80%98stop%20the%20boats'%20that%20surreptitiously%20carry%20illegal%20immigrants%20across%20the%20Channel%20to%20England's%20south%20coast%3B%20those%20deeply%20hazardous%20sea%20crossings%20are%20still%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%20has%20tried%20to%20appease%20the%20populist%20right-wing%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20by%20backing%20out%20of%20some%20key%20targets%20to%20tackle%20climate%20change%20and%20abandoning%20an%20expensive%20high-speed%20rail%20link%20from%20London%20to%20the%20north%20of%20England.%20Those%20decisions%20were%20not%20popular%20with%20the%20voters%20and%20didn't%20satisfy%20Sunak's%20critics%20within%20the%20party.%20In%20political%20terms%2C%20it's%20a%20lose-lose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Resurgent%20Opposition%20And%20A%20Threat%20From%20The%20Right%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20biggest%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20opposition%20has%20been%20reborn.%20The%20Labour%20Party%2C%20which%20spent%20several%20years%20heading%20so%20far%20left%20that%20it%20barely%20appeared%20on%20the%20political%20spectrum%2C%20has%20been%20refashioned%20as%20a%20pragmatic%2C%20centre-left%20party%20with%20a%20conspicuously%20competent%20and%20cautious%20leader%2C%20Keir%20Starmer.%20The%20Labour%20Party%20is%20once%20again%20seen%20as%20fit%20to%20govern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20double%20Sunak's%20difficulties%2C%20he%20also%20faces%20a%20threat%20from%20the%20right.%20The%20Reform%20Party%2C%20which%20was%20born%20out%20of%20the%20successful%20campaign%20to%20pull%20Britain%20out%20of%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20is%20now%20demanding%20much%20tighter%20restrictions%20on%20immigration%20and%20an%20emphasis%20on%20English%20nationalism.%