Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAndre%20Maxwell%20got%20a%20remote%20job%20as%20a%20solutions%20architect%20at%20Okta%20in%20March%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20picked%20up%20his%20laptop%20in%20Dallas%20and%20continued%20life%20as%20a%20digital%20nomad%20traveling%20to%2016%20countries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMaxwell%20was%20promoted%20to%20senior%20management%20and%20said%20performance%20was%20the%20most%20important%20factor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Andre%20Maxwell%2C%20a%20digital%20nomad%20who%20works%20at%20cloud%20security%20company%20Okta.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20Tulum%2C%20Mexico%2C%20when%20I%20joined%20Okta%20in%20March%202022%20as%20a%20solutions%20architect.%20I%20had%20already%20been%20a%20digital%20nomad%20for%20almost%20a%20year%2C%20working%20as%20a%20cybersecurity%20engineer%20at%20a%20smaller%20tech%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20companies%20were%20still%20primarily%20remote%20first%2C%20and%20my%20role%20at%20Okta%20was%20remote.%20I%20applied%20and%20went%20through%20the%20interview%20process%20online.%20When%20I%20got%20the%20job%2C%20I%20picked%20up%20my%20computer%20in%20Dallas.%20That's%20where%20my%20permanent%20address%20and%20stuff%20were%20%E2%80%94%20the%20latter%20in%20a%20storage%20unit.%20I%20continued%20traveling%20from%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20I%20have%20visited%2016%20countries%2C%20including%20Thailand%2C%20Japan%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Finland%2C%20Austria%2C%20and%20more.%20I%20change%20locations%20every%20few%20weeks%20to%20months.%20Mine%20is%20a%20unique%20lifestyle%2C%20but%20I%20believe%20in%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20logistics%20of%20working%20remotely%20while%20traveling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%209%20a.m.%20to%205%20p.m.%20Central%20Time%2C%20Monday%20through%20Friday%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20I%20am.%20I%20adjusted%20my%20sleep%20schedule%20to%20adhere%20to%20my%20company's%20work%20schedule%20when%20I%20started%20traveling.%20I%20start%20working%20at%205%20p.m.%20local%20time%20from%20Dubai%20or%2010%20p.m.%20from%20Japan.%20I%20normally%20get%20into%20the%20new%20rhythm%20within%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20good%20internet%20is%20always%20my%20top%20priority%20%E2%80%94%20I%20plan%20ahead%20before%20I%20travel%20to%20a%20new%20location.%20I've%20worked%20from%20places%20that%20generally%20don't%20have%20the%20most%20reliable%20infrastructure.%20When%20I%20was%20in%20Tulum%2C%20they%20often%20have%20power%20outages%20due%20to%20inclement%20weather.%20I%20mapped%20the%20locations%2C%20such%20as%20hotels%2C%20with%20backup%20generators%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20never%20lost%20internet%20or%20power%20while%20staying%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20sunny%2C%20coastal%20places%20in%20the%20US%2C%20like%20California%2C%20is%20much%20higher%20than%20in%20many%20countries%20I%20travel%20to.%20The%20lower%20living%20cost%20combined%20with%20my%20American%20salary%20offsets%20my%20traveling%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETraveling%20means%20I%20can%20live%20my%20best%20life%20in%20the%20sun%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20travel%20to%20places%20where%20I%20would%20have%20to%20start%20working%20in%20the%20morning.%20As%20a%20night%20owl%2C%20I%20prefer%20to%20have%20the%20day%20to%20myself%20and%20to%20work%20at%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20working%20on%20Central%20Time%20from%20Barcelona%20works%20for%20me%20since%20I%20start%20at%203%20or%204%20p.m.%20If%20I'm%20an%20emotional%20dump%20and%20not%20feeling%20good%2C%20I%20can%20take%20the%20day%20to%20myself%20because%20of%20the%20time%20difference.%20I%20wake%20up%2C%20sit%20in%20my%20thoughts%2C%20do%20something%20that%20makes%20me%20happy%2C%20and%20mentally%20recover%20before%20I%20start%20the%20workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20chase%20summer.%20I%20cannot%20stand%20being%20cold.%20In%20the%20morning%2C%20I%20go%20for%20a%20walk.%20I%20will%20get%20breakfast%20and%20go%20to%20the%20gym.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20my%20travels%20are%20inspired%20by%20food.%20I'm%20a%20foodie%20at%20heart.%20Discovering%20new%20restaurants%20and%20caf%C3%A9s%20in%20a%20coastal%20city%2C%20near%20the%20water%20with%20the%20sun%20shining%20on%20me%20%E2%80%94%20it%20makes%20the%20sacrifices%20of%20the%20digital%20nomad%20life%20all%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20people%2C%20not%20seeing%20their%20family%2C%20adjusting%20sleep%20schedules%2C%20and%20living%20out%20of%20a%20suitcase%20would%20be%20unbearable.%20But%20I%20am%20living%20my%20dream%20life%2C%20and%20those%20sacrifices%20don't%20feel%20as%20big.%20I%20talk%20to%20my%20family%20often.%20Seeing%20new%20places%2C%20chasing%20the%20sun%2C%20and%20making%20new%20experiences%20are%20more%20important%20than%20a%20sense%20of%20routine%20in%20a%20familiar%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20I%20got%20promoted%20while%20working%20remotely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20promoted%20to%20senior%20management%20in%20January.%20I%20am%20in%20my%20late%2020s.%20While%20I%20am%20relatively%20young%20for%20this%20position%20compared%20to%20what%20some%20would%20say%20is%20%26quot%3Bindustry%20average%2C%26quot%3B%20I've%20got%2010%20years%20of%20experience.%20Having%20this%20depth%20of%20knowledge%20helped%20me%20succeed%20in%20my%20new%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20for%20the%20promotion%20and%20went%20through%20the%20application%20process.%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20I%20was%20up%20against%20competition%2C%20but%20I%20got%20promoted%20because%20I'm%20known%20for%20good%20work.%20Being%20known%20for%20stellar%20work%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20go%20up%20within%20the%20ranks%20of%20any%20organization.%20My%20work-life%20balance%20contributes%20to%20my%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20digital%20nomad%20has%20never%20been%20a%20problem%20at%20work.%20I%20perform%20well%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20matters%20to%20my%20company.%20I%20never%20let%20anything%20happening%20in%20my%20personal%20life%20affect%20my%20work%20life.%20My%20career%20is%20something%20I%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20pride%20in.%20I%20still%20want%20to%20excel.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20helped%20me%20get%20to%20the%20position%20I%20am%20in%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20go%20into%20management%20to%20focus%20on%20streamlining%20business%20processes%20%E2%80%94%20how%20my%20team%20operates%2C%20the%20best%20way%20to%20engage%20with%20our%20customers%2C%20and%20providing%20them%20with%20the%20best%20possible%20quality.%20The%20people%20I%20manage%20are%20also%20remote%2C%20and%20we%20all%20work%20independently%20so%20an%20office%20environment%20wouldn't%20benefit%20our%20workflow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20don't%20have%20FOMO%20about%20working%20in%20an%20office%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20concerned%20about%20returning%20to%20an%20office%20because%20I've%20been%20customer-facing%20my%20entire%20career.%20If%20your%20role%20mainly%20depends%20on%20you%20and%20your%20ability%20to%20perform%2C%20then%20I%20think%20it's%20much%20easier%20to%20go%20the%20digital%20nomad%20route.%20People%20who%20work%20as%20part%20of%20a%20tight%20team%20have%20less%20flexibility%20and%20might%20benefit%20from%20face%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20might%20have%20enjoyed%20the%20community%20aspect%20at%20an%20office%20and%20happy%20hours%2C%20but%20I've%20never%20experienced%20it%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20feel%20worse%20off%20without%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20meet%20new%20people%20all%20the%20time%20traveling.%20More%20than%20I'd%20meet%20if%20I%20were%20working%20in%20the%20same%20office%20every%20day%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20feel%20I'm%20missing%20out%20on%20any%20of%20the%20personal%20aspects%20of%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20employee's%20value%20also%20depends%20on%20their%20happiness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20healthy%20work-life%20balance%20produces%20better%20work%20results.%20Leaving%20work%20and%20being%20in%20a%20new%20area%20you%20love%20simulates%20the%20brain%20differently.%20I%20work%20better%20because%20my%20travels%20make%20me%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20my%20job.%20Every%20new%20environment%20I%20enter%2C%20every%20new%20city%20or%20country%20restarts%20my%20happiness.%20A%20psychologically%20healthy%20person%20is%20more%20valuable%20to%20a%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-worker-promoted-senior-manager-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712221870000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660d67f21caec1275a6c4eca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-worker-promoted-senior-manager-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Digital%20nomad%20Andre%20Maxwell%20has%20always%20worked%20completely%20remotely.%20He%20said%20traveling%20and%20being%20happy%20means%20he%20performs%20better%20at%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Cornelia%20Holzbauer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-worker-promoted-senior-manager-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Probe%20agencies%20working%20for%20BJP'%3A%20Mamata%20at%20Bengal%20rally%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712221836000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109031152%2Cimgsize-872677.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Flok-sabha-polls-mamata-banerjee-says-probe-agencies-working-for-bjp-seeks-level-playing-field%2Farticleshow%2F109030287.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22West%20Bengal%20Chief%20Minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20during%20a%20public%20rally%20in%20Co