tion%20scheme%20in%202005-06%2C%20under%20which%20subsidies%20were%20provided%20for%20drip%20and%20sprinkler%20irrigation.%20Saravanan%2C%20an%20early%20adopter%20of%20many%20such%20new%3Cbr%3Eschemes%2C%20decided%20to%20give%20drip%20irrigation%20a%20try.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20face%20water%20scarcity%2C%20which%20made%20irrigation%20very%20difficult.%20Drip%20irrigation%20saves%20water%20and%20irrigates%20thrice%20the%20amount%20of%20land%20using%20the%20same%20water%20used%20by%20traditional%20methods%2C%E2%80%9D%20Saravanan%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202007%2C%20the%20farmer%20has%20moved%20to%20drip%20irrigation%20on%20his%206%20acre%20and%2036%20cents%20(1%20acre%20is%20100%20cents)%20land%20on%20which%20he%20cultivates%20turmeric%2C%20groundnuts%2C%20and%20vegetables.%20He%20also%20practises%20integrated%20farming%2C%20a%20sustainable%20agricultural%20system%20where%20crops%2C%20livestock%2C%20aquaculture%2C%20poultry%20are%20managed%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20these%20crops%2C%20he%20also%20manages%20livestock%2C%20including%20cows%2C%20goats%2C%20ducks%20and%20birds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20he%20started%20drip%20irrigation%2C%20he%20got%20his%20soil%20tested.%20The%20test%20indicated%20that%20the%20soil%20was%20not%20healthy%2C%20and%20had%20rising%20pH%20levels%20and%20was%20getting%20spoilt.%20This%20was%20the%20same%20time%20when%20his%20turmeric%20crop%20was%20affected%20by%20diseases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan3-1712146605.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Saravanan%20uses%20innovative%20methods%20of%20farming%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan3-1712146605.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan3-1712146605-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan3-1712146605-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan3-1712146605-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fsaravanan3-1712146605-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346396%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESaravanan%20uses%20innovative%20methods%20of%20farming%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20at%20the%20KVK%20suggested%20some%20biofertilisers%20to%20salvage%20the%20turmeric%20crop%2C%20and%20it%20worked.%20They%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20only%20way%20to%20preserve%20the%20soil%20and%20prevent%20further%20damage%20was%20by%20moving%20to%20organic%20farming%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20the%2058-year-old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20in%202008%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20save%20his%20land%2C%20soil%20and%20crops%2C%20he%20slowly%20stopped%20using%20chemical%20fertilisers%20and%20pesticides.%20He%20also%20started%20practising%20crop%20rotation%20to%20ensure%20soil%20health.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20I%20plant%20pulses%2C%20I%20ensure%20that%20I%20change%20the%20crop%20for%20the%20next%20year.%20I%20also%20planted%20nerium%20as%20a%20border%20crop%20to%20absorb%20pollutants%20and%20grow%20%3Cem%3Eagathi%20%3C%2Fem%3E%26amp%3B%20maize%20around%20the%20field%20as%20a%20barrier%20crop%20to%20prevent%20the%20entry%20of%20pests%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20constructed%20a%20vermicompost%20production%20unit%20in%202008%20which%20produces%20over%206%20tonnes%20per%20year.%20He%20uses%20this%20vermicompost%2C%20neem%20cakes%20and%20castor%20cakes%20as%20fertilisers.%20He%20also%20has%20a%20biogas%20plant%20that%20converts%20the%20waste%20into%20energy%20and%20purifies%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20these%2C%20he%20utilises%20%3Cem%3Epanchakavya%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20solution%20made%20of%20cow%E2%80%99s%20milk%2C%20curd%2C%20ghee%2C%20cow%20dung%20and%20urine%20used%20as%20a%20fertiliser)%20spray%20in%20addition%20to%20a%20homemade%20spray%20containing%20ginger%2C%20garlic%20%26amp%3B%20chillies%20for%20controlling%20pests%20and%20disease.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20everything%20was%20going%20well%2C%20Saravanan%20found%20it%20tough%20to%20grow%20fodder%20for%20his%20cattle.%20Buying%20it%20from%20outside%20was%20expensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20then%2C%20in%202011%2C%20KVK%20Namakkal%20conducted%20a%20demonstration%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F336600%2Ftech-nursery-hydroponics-aeroponics-farming-ratlam-brothers-arbind-ravindra-dhakad%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoilless%20hydroponic%20farming%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20maize.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGrowing%20maize%20in%20a%20cupboard%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20696px)%20100vw%2C%20696px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-04-02-at-7.26.52-PM-1712146072.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22696%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Saravanan%20grows%20maize%20fodder%20in%20his%20cupboard%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-04-02-at-7.26.52-PM-1712146072.jpeg%20696w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-04-02-at-7.26.52-PM-1712146072-245x300.jpeg%20245w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-04-02-at-7.26.52-PM-1712146072-500x613.jpeg%20500w%2C%2