www.thebetterindia.com%2F85574%2Fbera-rajasthan-leopards-mount-abu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereveres%20the%20leopards%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Hartnaram%2C%20who%20is%20a%20Rabari%20herdsman%E2%80%99s%20son%20shared%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20burst%20firecrackers%20during%20Diwali%20and%20refrain%20from%20playing%20loud%20music%20even%20during%20wedding%20processions%20so%20that%20it%20does%20not%20disturb%20the%20wild%20cats.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20mutual%20respect%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20the%20recipe%20for%20the%20harmony.%20And%20seconding%20this%20thought%20is%20a%20conservationist%20Shatrunjay%20Pratap%20Singh%20from%20Jaipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20call%20of%20the%20wilderness%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBe%20certain%20that%20a%20leopard%20will%20not%20harm%20you%20if%20you%20are%20with%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Rabari%20community.%20This%20is%20their%20promise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20threatened%20to%20have%20their%20population%20depleted%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F246169%2Fladakh-snow-leopard-conservancy-india-trust-saviours-rinchen-wangchuk-tsewang-namgail-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20leopards%20now%20enjoy%20the%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20have.%20And%20as%20any%20local%20will%20tell%20you%20it%20is%20Singh%20behind%20this%20achievement.%20Now%20heading%20the%20Bera%20Safari%20Lodge%2C%20a%20boutique%20homestay%20in%20the%20Bera%20village%20of%20Jawai%2C%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20journey%20is%20not%20simply%20one%20of%20a%20man%20setting%20up%20a%20resort.%20Rather%2C%20it%20is%20a%20lesson%20in%20perseverance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fconservation--1710483249.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Bera%20Safari%20Lodge%20in%20Jawai%2C%20Rajasthan%20is%20a%20sustainable%20property%20that%20believes%20being%20in%20harmony%20with%20nature%20and%20the%20wild%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fconservation--1710483249.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fconservation--1710483249-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fconservation--1710483249-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fconservation--1710483249-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fconservation--1710483249-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344903%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Bera%20Safari%20Lodge%20in%20Jawai%2C%20Rajasthan%20is%20a%20sustainable%20property%20that%20believes%20being%20in%20harmony%20with%20nature%20and%20the%20wild%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Singh%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20Singh%20was%20on%20vacation%20at%20his%20ancestral%20farmland%20in%20Pindwara%2C%2020%20km%20from%20Bera.%20One%20afternoon%2C%20while%20watching%20the%20leopards%20%E2%80%94%20a%20passion%20he%20had%20developed%20ever%20since%20nature%20walks%20during%20his%20boarding%20school%20days%20at%20St%20Mary%E2%80%99s%20in%20Mount%20Abu%20%E2%80%94%20he%20heard%20a%20blast.%20%E2%80%9CI%20enquired%20with%20the%20locals%20about%20the%20source%20of%20the%20blast%20and%20learnt%20that%20the%20Government%20had%20allotted%20nine%20mines%20in%20the%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares%2C%20adding%20that%20further%20probing%20revealed%20144%20mines%20were%20in%20the%20pipeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20these%20blasts%20and%20loud%20noises%20continued%20for%20mining%20purposes%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F251019%2Fwildlife-rescue-kashmir-woman-teacher-leopard-bear-aaliya-mir-math-teacher-animal-human-conflict-yos191%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleopards%E2%80%99%20habitats%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%2C%20along%20with%20a%20few%20locals%2C%20and%20with%20the%20help%20and%20support%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20Forest%20Department%20led%20by%20then%20DFO%20(Divisional%20Forest%20Officer)%20of%20Pali%20%E2%80%94%20IFS%20Balaji%20Kari%20%E2%80%94%20put%20their%20heads%20together%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20stop%20this%20from%20snowballing%20into%20a%20catastrophe.%20But%20as%20they%20would%20soon%20discover%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20that%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20spent%20the%20majority%20of%20three%20years%20having%20countless%20meetings%20with%20government%20officials%2C%20bureaucrats%20and%20ministers%20where%20he%20convinced%20the%20room%20that%20Jawai%20was%20the%20natural%20habitat%20of%20leopards%2C%20and%20that%20the%20area%20housed%20tremendous%20tourism%20potential.%20In%202014%2C%20the%20Government%20gave%20a%20premature%20termination%20notice%20to%20all%20the%20mines.%20The%20activity%20was%20soon%20discontinued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%2C%20who%20had%20quit%20a%20lucrative%20job%20in%20winemaking%20to%20turn%20his%20attention%20to%20the%20matter%2C%20now%20had%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F179096%2Fifs-officer-hero-mumbai-leopard-human-conflict-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20dream%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20envisioned%20that%20the%20land%20that%20he%20had%20fought%20so%20hard%20to%20protect%20would%20now%20be%20a%20safe%20haven%20for%20the%20leopards%20and%20those%20who%20loved%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20Bera%20Safari%20Lodge%20stands%20on%20eight%20acres%20of%20land%20and%20is%20a%20gold%20standard%20in%20how%20luxury%20does%20not%20need%20to%20be%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20success%20story%20in%20conservation%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%2C%20who%20is%20now%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20a%20successful%20boutique%20lodge%2C%20recalls%20his%20early%20days%20of%20renting%20out%20a%20room%20in%20his%20driver%E2%80%99s%20home.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20at%20the%20same%20time%20that%20I%20was%20fighting%20against%20the%20mining%20in%20the%20area.%20I%20had%20to%20stay%20on-site%2C%20so%20I%20lived%20with%20my%20driver%20who%20was%20a%20local%20in%20Bera.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20lot%20of%20criticism.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20used%20to%20make%20fun%20of%20me%20saying%20that%20I%20was%20living%20with%20my%20driver.%20But%20someone%20had%20to%20fight%20the%20mining%20project%20and%20I%20was%20very%20passionate%20about%20it.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F36889%2Finternational-day-of-snow-leopard%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20agenda%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20very%20clear.%20I%20thought%2C%20if%20nobody%20does%20it%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20doing%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20observation%20on%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20part%20has%20been%20the%20attitude%20of%20the%20locals%20towards%20the%20leopards.%20Once%20frightened%20about%20leopard%20attacks%2C%20he%20says%20the%20locals%20(aside%20from%20the%20Rabari%20community)%20would%20poison%20the%20beasts.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20today%2C%20due%20to%20the%20tourism%20model%20in%20Bera%2C%20every%20villager%20is%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20associated%20with%20it.%20Since%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20tourism%20here%20is%20safaris%20to%20see%20the%20leopard%2C%20they%20understand%20how%20important%20the%20animal%20is%20for%20their%20welfare.%20Today%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F12694%2Fvanamitra-suresh-conserve-wildlife-india-leopards%2F%5C%22%2